body:
Ten and Donna

Hi I’m here to talk about the tenth doctor and Donna’s relationship

iTS LITERALLY THE CUTEST THING??

Like they’re not or have never been romantically inclined but they love each other so much?? He grabs her hand when they run together, her constantly puts his hand on her shoulder or back, they’re such an amazing dynamic friendship, like yes she drives him up the wall but they love each other so so much.

In conclusion I love Donna Nobel and the Doctor they’re the best doctor / companion duo (with team TARDIS a close second)

blog.description: "Rose, before I go, I just want to tell you you were fantastic. Absolutely fantastic. And do you know what? So was I!" - 9

body:
Rant

(If you don’t want to read the whole thing, scroll down and only read the last paragraph.)

I just need to get this of my chest. The few days I have been on here (and also the longer time on Instagram) I experienced so so much hate towards different characters, actors and writers and it bothers me a lot!

For example: someone posts something about Martha and I know that I don’t want to read the comments because half of it will be “ugh I hate Martha, she always was so jealous of Rose, I miss Rose, f*ck Martha” and the other half of it will be “Martha was SO underrated! I never liked rose and that the Doctor used Martha just as a filler makes me hate Rose even more!”

Can’t I love Rose and still like Martha and acknowledge that she was as important as the rest?

It’s the same with any other character. There is always a controversy. Instead of appreciating the things we like about the characters we turn them into different poles, enemies and if you like one of them you have to hate the other.

If the official doctor who page posts a throwback there will be under guarantee lot’s of comments like “Back to the era where doctor who was still great with david Tennant and without Chibnalls shitty writing”

Uhm.. no?

Yes. Yes I’m nostalgic too. Yes I loved Tennants era. YES.

But I also love every other Doctor. I love Jodie and Christopher and Matt and Peter and don’t forget about classic who!

And I don’t think Chibnals writing is bad. It’s different. But that’s what Doctor Who is about. Isn’t it? About change. Nothing lasts forever.

There are also a lot of people here who hate Moffat. And I genuinely DON’T understand? Like yeah, he did things to the characters that hurt. I mean like.. a lot. But he also was the one who breathed life into them! Without him they wouldn’t exist and my respect for his writing is so huge!

In short: I’m not saying you have to love everyone. I’m not saying you can’t prefere one over another. That’s just natural. But all the hate is so unjustified and instead of strengthening the bonds in this community it might have the power to tear it appart completely.

I’m closing this rant with a quote of the Doctor we should all keep in mind.

“900 years of time and space and I never met anyone who wasn’t important.” - The Doctor
